dismissalText.commentary: Soumya Sarkar c sub (SS Cottrell) b Reifer 66 (41b 9x4 3x6) SR: 160.97

dismissalComment.html: full, very wide outside off, and he throws his hands at this. Tries to slap it over long off, but toe-ends the shot. Cottrell makes no mistake running in from long off. Replays suggest that Reifer had overstepped but a closer look suggests that it's a legal ball. The foot had dragged out of the crease after the initial contact with the ground. Huge wicket

dismissalComment.html: down the track again, and this time Gabriel bangs it in short, invites Tamim to hit the shoulder-high ball over mid-off. Goes through with the shot, ends up hitting it high rather than far, and he ends up hitting it down the throat of Holder at mid-off. An exchange of words between Gabriel and Tamim as he makes his way off the ground

headshotImage.caption: Sabbir Rahman headshot
headshotImage.longCaption: Sabbir Rahman headshot

dismissalComment.html: big appeal, given! Back of a length, and it nips in and keeps a touch low, maybe. Looks to work it leg side and the ball beats his inside edge and hits front pad. Given out by Richard Kettleborough, and there's no DRS, so Sabbir will have to walk back even though it may juuust have been going down leg. We'll have to watch a few replays to know for sure

commentTextItems.html: Bangladesh win their first ever ODI tournament final! Historic as Mahmudullah crashes a cover drive through the off side

commentPostTextItems.html: 7.46pm That's all from us at ESPNcricinfo. Hope you enjoyed our coverage of this historic Bangladesh win. A lot for Jason Holder and West Indies to worry out. Keep an eye out on our website tomorrow morning, because West Indies are supposed to release their final World Cup squad then. Till then, it's goodbye.
Azweer: "@Tamim Sarker: so it's gonna be a double dhamaka in Dhaka"
7.41pm Smiles in the Bangladesh camp. Mortaza hugs coach Rhodes after giving a mighty cuddle to Soumya Sarkar
Shishir : "Finally first multinational tournament trophy!! Congratulations Bangla Tigers!! From Nepal!!"
Aj : "For the love of God Keemo Paul in for Roach please "
Shuvashish Roy: "We have never seen such well-poised and synchronised Bangladesh cricket team before. This would be our World Cup. #ShabashBangladesh"
Azweer: "So tomorrow will be a national holiday in Bangladesh....!!!"
Noise.of.silenc: "-What do we say to the GOD of cricket??? -NOT TODAY! ;)"
Tamim Sarker: "@Azweer- Its already national holiday for us tomorrow! Buddha Purnima"
Hridoy: "Mosaddek was 7 from 9 ball. And reached fifty in 20th ball. This is some hitting."
Dr. Engr. Md. M: "Congratulations Bangladesh Cricket Team for the wonderful victory. Worth to see the match without sleeping."

7.40pm Terrific scenes in the Bangladesh camp. They've won with seven balls to spare. It wasn't easy, with Shakib unavailable, but they were terrific in the last four overs of West Indies' innings after which their batsmen kept the tempo going through the innings. First, it was Soumya Sarkar, who struck a half-century in 27 balls. Mushfiqur Rahim chipped in too, but when it mattered, Mosaddek Hossain stood up to take his team through.
ador: "Wonderful batting display, wonderful Soumya, wonderful Mosaddek! "

commentTextItems.html: length ball, on off, and he defends!
slower ball, full outside off, and driven to deep point. Scores are level
length ball, just outside off and going through to the keeper
full, just outside off, and tapped to cover
length ball on middle, and tucked away to square leg. He'll keep strike

commentPostTextItems.html: Fastest ODI fifty for Bangladesh from Mosaddek

commentTextItems.html: length ball on middle, and clipped off his pads to deep midwicket. Half-century for Mosaddek
holy guacamole! Full, on leg, and Mosaddek exposes all three stumps before playing a beautiful inside-out six over cover
another one! Bangladesh are romping home now. Quicker from Allen, and Mosaddek is halfway down the track, but he sticks his bat out to play a late cut for four. Delicate
Hossain the hero! Full, on off, and he comes down the wicket to lift a six over long off! The crowd's ecstatic

commentPreTextItems.html: Bangladesh need 27 off 18. If this was a T20 game, you'd back them. Right? Riiiight?

commentTextItems.html: switch hit for six! Half-tracker on middle, but he goes left-handed right away, and then slogs it over the point boundary for half-a-dozen. How about that?
yorker, on off. Dug away to third man

commentPostTextItems.html: tadj: "that was some ordinary and defensive minded captaincy from holder, u hadda search for the wicket even if its a 12 run over should have gone gabriel "

full toss, wide outside off, but manages to drag a shot to wide long on. Can't keep it down to a single
nearly a yorker, just outside off, and guided down to third man
much needed six! In the slot outside off, nad Mosaddek stays on the back foot before muscling a lofted shot over extra cover. Powerful

commentPostTextItems.html: Aranya: "What you meant to say was "We're in the endgame now"."

commentPreTextItems.html: Alright then. We're in the business end of this game. Bangladesh need 39 off four overs.

dismissalText.commentary: Soumya Sarkar c sub (SS Cottrell) b Reifer 66 (41b 9x4 3x6) SR: 160.97

dismissalComment.html: full, very wide outside off, and he throws his hands at this. Tries to slap it over long off, but toe-ends the shot. Cottrell makes no mistake running in from long off. Replays suggest that Reifer had overstepped but a closer look suggests that it's a legal ball. The foot had dragged out of the crease after the initial contact with the ground. Huge wicket
